Karel travelled from London to Johannesburg and then from Johannesburg to Windhoek.

\begin{parts}
\item The flight from London to Johannesburg took 11 hours 10 minutes.
The average speed was 813 km/h.

Calculate the distance travelled from London to Johannesburg.
Give your answer correct to the nearest 10 km.

\AnswerLine[][] km
\Marks{3}

\item The total time for Karel's journey from London to Windhoek was 15 hours 42 minutes.
The total distance travelled from London to Windhoek was 10 260 km.

\begin{subparts}
\item Calculate the average speed for this journey.

\AnswerLine[][] km/h
\Marks{2}

\item The cost of Karel's journey from London to Windhoek was \$470.

\begin{subsubparts}
\item Calculate the distance travelled per dollar.

\AnswerLine[][] km per dollar
\Marks{1}

\item Calculate the cost per 100 km of this journey.
Give your answer correct to the nearest cent.

\$ \AnswerLine[][] per 100 km
\Marks{2}
\end{subsubparts}
\end{subparts}

\item Karel changed \$300 into 3891 Namibian dollars.

Complete the statement.

\$1 = \AnswerLine[][] Namibian dollars
\Marks{1}

\end{parts}

